---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const updated = 'July 20, 2026';
---
<Layout title="Privacy Policy — AI Tech Blog" description="Privacy policy for AI Tech Blog: how this site uses cookies, analytics, and advertising services.">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-2 text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-100">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-8">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200">
      <p>
        This privacy policy explains what information is collected when you visit
        <strong>AI Tech Blog</strong> (https://b1ackjack12.github.io/) and how it is used.
        This is a personal blog operated by an individual; it does not require accounts,
        does not have comment forms, and does not collect personal information directly.
      </p>

      <h2>Information Collected Automatically</h2>
      <p>
        Like most websites, this site uses third-party services that may collect
        information automatically through cookies and similar technologies:
      </p>

      <h3>Google Analytics</h3>
      <p>
        This site uses Google Analytics to understand how visitors use the site (pages
        visited, time on page, approximate location at city level, device and browser
        type). This data is aggregated and does not identify you personally. You can
        opt out with the
        <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Google AdSense</h3>
      <p>
        This site displays advertisements served by Google AdSense. Google and its
        partners use advertising cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this
        and other websites. Specifically:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on a
          user's prior visits to this website or other websites.
        </li>
        <li>
          Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads
          based on your visits to this site and/or other sites on the Internet.
        </li>
        <li>
          You may opt out of personalized advertising by visiting
          <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a>,
          or opt out of a broader set of third-party vendors' cookies at
          <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.aboutads.info</a>.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files stored by your browser. Beyond the third-party
        cookies described above, this site stores a single local preference
        (your light/dark theme choice) in your browser's local storage. It never leaves
        your device. You can block or delete cookies at any time through your browser
        settings; the site remains fully readable without them.
      </p>

      <h2>External Links</h2>
      <p>
        Posts link to external sites (documentation, papers, tools). This policy applies
        only to this site — external sites have their own privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Data Retention and Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        This site does not sell, trade, or otherwise transfer information to outside
        parties. Analytics data is retained according to Google Analytics' standard
        retention settings.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If this policy changes, the updated version will be posted on this page with a
        revised "last updated" date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact
        <a href="mailto:bumjun0097@gmail.com">bumjun0097@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
